subSubSection.paragraph:
Sertularella peculiaris

shares some features with 

S. robusta

Coughtrey, 
1876


, as follows: 
1
) colonies with both stolonal and erect growth forms; 
2
) stems always monosiphonic; 
3
) hydrothecae flask-shaped, with slightly swollen basal part, narrowing distally, rim slightly everted; walls provided with a number of external ribs; several internal projections of perisarc below aperture; 
4
) gonothecae elongated-ovoid; walls with a number of external folds; aperture encircled by projections of perisarc.
